            <p>New York<lb/>
                13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June&#91;<lb/>inserted by author&#93;87.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr <sic>Morias</sic><lb/></p>
            <p>It was Mr Wetzlar&#39;s<lb/> and my intention&#44; to have<lb/> called on you to bid you<lb/> farewell&#44; before our departure<lb/> from Philadelphia as we<lb/> expect for the future to<lb/> make our home in<lb/> Montreal but <sic>realy</sic> had not<lb/> time&#45;&#45;so now my dear Mr<lb/> <sic>Morias</sic> take this opportu<lb/>nity to bid you good bye<lb/> and thank you for your<lb/> kindness and attention <del>in</del><lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>during our sad affliction<lb/> at the death of our Son<lb/> and shall ever have the<lb/> <sic>rememberance</sic> of you<lb/> with feelings of gratitude<lb/> Wishing you &#38; your<lb/> family health and all<lb/> the happiness that this<lb/> world can afford.<lb/>  Yours sincerely<lb/> <hi rend="underline">S Wetzlar</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>My daughter desires her<lb/> kindest regards to you &#38;<lb/> your circle<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Mr <sic>Morias</sic><lb/>
                <del>c&#47;o Mrs E. H. Weil<lb/>
                    1720 Pine St.<lb/>
                    546 North 5th St.<lb/> Philadelphia<lb/> Pa<lb/></del></p>
            </body>
